THE City of Cape Town has issued a notice of road closures for the Mandela Day Walk/ Jog scheduled to take place on Sunday, 22 July, 2018.  The event kicks off at 10 am at the Cape Town City Hall, and roads around the area will be closed from 9 am onwards.  The lane restrictions will apply along the route in order to minimise traffic disruptions and residents and motorists are advised to use alternate routes as temporary lane restrictions and road closures will be in place for the duration of the event.  The following roads will be closed:  